{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}
{% block body %}
    {% set bucketList = ["bungee jumping","living in Peking, China","horse riding and caravan cruise in Kazakhstan","Hozier's concert","sandboarding","underwater restaurant","visiting Vietnam","visit Turkey's most famous baklava shop","be invited to a big Indian wedding","Visit Egypt", "See northern lights","finish writing my book"]  %}
    {% set imgBucketList=["bungeeJumping","china","horseridingKazakhstan","hozier","sandboarding","underwaterRestaurant","vietnam","baklava","indianWedding","egypt","northernLights","bookwriting"] %}
    {% set paragraphs =["Someone would want to bungee jump to confront their deepest fears in a single, exhilarating moment. It’s the ultimate test of trust—in the equipment, the crew, and oneself—proving that you can step into the void and come out the other side not just intact, but euphoric. For many, it’s about shattering personal limitations; the act serves as a powerful, physical metaphor for overcoming obstacles, leaving the jumper with a lasting sense of invincibility and a unique story of radical surrender.",
    "A person would choose to live in Peking (Beijing) to immerse themselves in the dynamic tension of ancient history colliding with hyper-modernity. It offers the chance to walk the same hutongs (alleyways) as dynasties past while standing beneath the futuristic architecture of the CBD. Living there provides a deep, unmediated understanding of China’s complex culture, from its world-renowned culinary scene to its political heart, allowing a resident to move beyond the role of tourist and into the rhythm of a city that is quite literally shaping the 21st century.",
    "One would embark on horse riding and a caravan cruise in Kazakhstan to experience the romance of the nomadic lifestyle that defined the Silk Road. It’s a call to disconnect from digital life and reconnect with raw nature across the vast, hauntingly beautiful steppe and the Tien Shan mountains. This journey offers a unique form of cultural immersion, traveling as the locals have for centuries, fostering a deep sense of self-reliance and offering the rare privilege of experiencing true, uninterrupted silence and star-filled skies.",
    "Attending a Hozier concert is about seeking a shared, almost spiritual experience centered on masterful musicianship and deeply poetic lyricism. His music blends blues, folk, and soul to explore themes of love, humanity, and social justice, creating an atmosphere that is both intensely intimate and powerfully communal. A fan would go to feel the visceral rawness of his voice live, to stand among a crowd of like-minded people who find solace and catharsis in songs that feel like modern hymns, leaving them emotionally moved and inspired.",
    "Someone would want to try sandboarding for the unique thrill of surfing down towering, golden dunes in a landscape that feels otherworldly. Unlike snowboarding, it offers a warmer climate and the surreal visual of carving tracks on vast seas of sand, often in iconic desert locations. It combines the adrenaline of a high-speed sport with the serene, almost alien beauty of the desert, appealing to adventure seekers who want to try something novel and capture the perfect action shot against a stunning, minimalist backdrop.",
    "Dining in an underwater restaurant is driven by a desire to experience the ultimate fusion of luxury and the sublime. It’s about eating a meticulously prepared meal while marine life—from schools of fish to majestic rays—glides silently past the panoramic acrylic windows. A person would go not just for the food, but for the architectural wonder and the surreal feeling of being submerged in a new world, making the meal an unforgettable, multi-sensory event that blurs the line between adventure and fine dining.",
    "A traveler is drawn to Vietnam for its breathtaking diversity, from the emerald waters of Ha Long Bay to the terraced rice fields of Sapa and the bustling energy of Ho Chi Minh City. It offers an unmatched culinary journey, where street-side pho and banh mi are as celebrated as any fine dining. Beyond the landscapes and food, people visit Vietnam for its resilient spirit and warm hospitality, seeking a country that offers a profound sense of history, incredible value, and a vibrant, fast-paced energy that is both chaotic and charming.",
    "One would seek out Turkey’s most famous baklava shop, such as Hafız Mustafa or Karaköy Güllüoğlu, to taste the absolute pinnacle of a centuries-old culinary art. It’s about understanding why this specific dessert is a national treasure—experiencing the perfect, paper-thin layers of phyllo, the precisely sourced pistachios, and the delicate, aromatic syrup that can’t be replicated abroad. For a food lover, it’s a pilgrimage to a cultural institution, a chance to enjoy a piece of living history served on a small plate with a glass of Turkish tea.",
    "Receiving an invitation to a big Indian wedding is a dream for many because it is the ultimate cultural extravaganza, often lasting several days and involving hundreds of guests. It’s an opportunity to experience unparalleled hospitality, vibrant music, intricate rituals, and a sensory overload of colors, flavors, and emotions. For an outsider, it offers a rare, immersive glimpse into the importance of family, tradition, and celebration in Indian culture, providing a front-row seat to a joyous, once-in-a-lifetime event that is often more elaborate and emotionally resonant than what is depicted in films.",
    "Visiting Egypt is a pilgrimage for anyone fascinated by the deep well of human history, offering the chance to stand in the shadow of the Great Pyramids of Giza and gaze upon the treasures of King Tutankhamun. It’s the opportunity to sail the Nile, the lifeblood of an ancient civilization, and to explore monumental temples like Karnak and Abu Simbel that defy comprehension. Beyond the ancient wonders, a visitor goes to experience the vibrant, bustling culture of modern Egypt, the legendary hospitality of its people, and the unique landscape where golden desert meets the fertile river valley.",
    "A person would chase the northern lights (Aurora Borealis) to witness one of nature’s most spectacular and humbling phenomena. It’s driven by a desire to see the impossible—curtains of green, pink, and purple light dancing across a dark, star-filled sky—an experience often described as magical or spiritual. This pursuit is also a commitment to adventure, often requiring travel to remote, Arctic locations, embracing the cold, and practicing patience for the chance to witness a fleeting display that puts the vastness of the universe into perspective.",
    "Finishing writing a book is the ultimate act of self-actualization for an aspiring author, transforming a nebulous idea into a tangible, complete reality. It represents the culmination of countless hours of discipline, creativity, and vulnerability, proving to oneself that they possess the stamina and skill to sustain a long-form project. The desire stems from the deep need to share a story or idea with the world, to join the ranks of published authors, and to finally silence the internal question of “what if?” by crossing the finish line of a monumental personal goal."] %}


    <div class="content">
        <h2>Welcome to the bucket list </h2>
        <p>This is a site where people can come to share what they wish to do at least once in their lives!</p>
        <p>Whether it's eating the flakiest, most delicious baklava of Turkey, or conquer you fear of heights by bungee jumping, dream as big as you can, but even small, modest dreams are just as important as the big ones.</p>
        <p>So share them, maybe you can make them come true ! ✨</p>
        <p>Here's a small example </p>

        <h3>List of things on my bucket list</h3>
        <div class="slideshow-container">

        {%for img in imgBucketList%}
        <div class="mySlides">
            <div class="numbertext">{{loop.index}}</div>
            <img src="{{ asset('images/'~ img ~'.jpg')}}" alt="{{ img }}">
            <div class="text">{{ bucketList[loop.index0] }}</div>

        </div>

        {%endfor%}

        <a class="prev" onclick="plusSlides(-1)">&#10094;</a>
        <a class="next" onclick="plusSlides(1)">&#10095;</a>
    </div>
    <br>

    {% for things in bucketList%}
        <div>{{ loop.index }}: <span>{{ things }}</span></div>
        <br>
        <div>{{ paragraphs[loop.index0] }}</div>
        <br>
    {% endfor %}
    </div>

    {% endblock %}

{% block extrastyle %}
    <style>
        body{

            background-image: url('{{ asset('images/7023263.jpg') }}'), linear-gradient(rgba(255, 255, 255, 08), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6)) ;
        }
        footer{
            margin-top: 10vh;
            background: linear-gradient(rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6));
            border-radius: 4px;
            padding:4px;
        }
    </style>
{% endblock %}
